JAKARTA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Bali provincial police said on Tuesday they had confiscated 35.17 kilograms of crystal methamphetamine and arrested three suspects in the province. Briefing on the largest narcotics case in Bali during the COVID-19 pandemic at a press conference, provincial chief of police, inspector general Putu Jayan Danu Putra said police officers had also seized 1,488 grams of ecstasy and 32 grams of cocaine. The suspects stored the narcotics in a villa and planned to sell it to foreigners visiting entertainment places in Seminyak, Canggu and Petitenget, said Putra, referring to a number of tourist areas in North Kuta town, Badung district. Investigations to map out the smuggling route and the involvement of other parties are underway.  â– 